442
00:26:11,879 --> 00:26:16,439
Wu can't possibly stay in your house forever.

443
00:26:17,439 --> 00:26:18,960
What do you mean?

444
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:23,919
Wu.

445
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,919
I have good news for you.

446
00:26:27,639 --> 00:26:28,800
We agreed

447
00:26:28,879 --> 00:26:31,600
that you should be my daughter-in-law.

448
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:34,000
What does it mean?

449
00:26:35,320 --> 00:26:36,199
Look.

450
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:39,480
I already brought you a duck.

451
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:40,720
Well,

452
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,960
consider this a bride price.

453
00:26:44,560 --> 00:26:47,879
Ma'am, we've already agreed on this.

454
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:49,879
My goodness.

455
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:51,159
Come on.

456
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:55,320
You know my situation very well.

457
00:26:55,399 --> 00:26:57,159
You have much to gain

458
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:59,560
if Wu marries my son.

459
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:04,840
I quite agree with her.

460
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,159
I disagree!

461
00:27:11,280 --> 00:27:12,159
XU XIANG, 13 YEARS OLD

462
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,320
Does your drooling son

463
00:27:14,399 --> 00:27:16,120
want Wu as his wife?

464
00:27:16,199 --> 00:27:17,600
In his dreams!

465
00:27:17,679 --> 00:27:18,919
Mind your words!

466
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,159
Is Wu very bright now?

467
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,720
She is just as dull.

468
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:26,040
She's perfect for my son.

469
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:27,520
No means no.

470
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:29,120
-Enough. -Wait.

471
00:27:29,199 --> 00:27:30,040
Doggy,

472
00:27:30,120 --> 00:27:31,439
do you fancy her now?

473
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:34,720
Your son is--

474
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:35,760
Goodness.

475
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:37,879
Sit down.

476
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,520
Stop shouting.

477
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:41,480
We'll let Wu pick.

478
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:43,280
All right, ma'am?

479
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:45,480
Ma'am.

480
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:48,040
You should give up on Wu.

481
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,399
Her noggin isn't good enough

482
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:50,399
to understand you.

483
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:53,360
I can decide for her.

484
00:27:53,439 --> 00:27:55,760
We have a lot of ducks here.

485
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,639
But we only have one Wu.

486
00:27:58,439 --> 00:28:00,600
This doesn't make sense.

487
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:01,919
Wu isn't even your daughter.

488
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,240
How can you decide for her?

489
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:05,199
Wu isn't my daughter,

490
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:07,159
so I can't marry her off to just anybody.

491
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:08,600
Ma'am,

492
00:28:08,679 --> 00:28:09,879
what if one day

493
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:12,480
her parents show up?

494
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:13,679
Imagine that.

495
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:15,879
How am I supposed to face them?

496
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:17,480
Nonsense!

497
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:20,320
You just want to keep her for your son!

498
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:24,520
Ma'am, I don't know about that.

499
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:25,960
But I do know that she isn't

500
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,560
going to be your daughter-in-law.

501
00:28:27,639 --> 00:28:30,000
Have fun raising those two idiots

502
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:31,560
all your life, then!

503
00:28:31,639 --> 00:28:33,159
Unbelievable!

504
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:35,560
Curse it!

505
00:28:35,639 --> 00:28:36,879
This is getting on my nerves!

506
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:40,320
Come inside.

507
00:28:46,280 --> 00:28:47,919
Listen, just now, you were--

508
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,679
Are you stupid?

509
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:53,040
Her son is dull.

510
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:55,000
And so is she.

511
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:56,720
No one in their right mind

512
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:58,320
would marry their daughter to her son.

513
00:28:58,399 --> 00:29:00,439
Are you trying to ruin Wu's life?

514
00:29:01,159 --> 00:29:03,520
But Wu can't stay with us forever.

515
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:05,240
She's an adult now.

516
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:06,959
It's not right.

517
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:08,280
When I'm free tomorrow,

518
00:29:08,360 --> 00:29:10,320
I'll take her to the town.

519
00:29:10,399 --> 00:29:11,959
I'll find her family. All right?

520
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:14,600
I guess that's the only option we have.

521
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:26,040
Dad, Mom,

522
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:28,120
even if we can't find her family,

523
00:29:28,199 --> 00:29:29,840
we can't throw her away.

524
00:29:33,959 --> 00:29:35,120
Can we

525
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:39,480
adopt her, then?

526
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:42,959
She is right!

527
00:29:43,040 --> 00:29:44,959
You do fancy her!

528
00:29:46,919 --> 00:29:49,080
Perhaps I can adopt her as my goddaughter.

529
00:29:49,159 --> 00:29:50,399
You'll have a sister.

530
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,360
Mom!

531
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:55,080
I've been thinking.

532
00:29:55,159 --> 00:29:57,080
If we cannot find her family,

533
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:59,320
we can only accept her

534
00:29:59,399 --> 00:30:00,480
as our family.

535
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:02,760
What do you mean?

536
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:04,959
Are you saying that she's stupid

537
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:06,720
or that our son isn't good enough for her?

538
00:30:06,800 --> 00:30:08,760
No, I don't think she's stupid at all.

539
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:10,800
I just think that she's so distant.

540
00:30:10,879 --> 00:30:12,080
She's so cold.

541
00:30:12,159 --> 00:30:13,879
Even a dog

542
00:30:13,959 --> 00:30:15,560
will show gratitude.

543
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:18,480
Do you think

544
00:30:18,560 --> 00:30:21,639
she treats us as her family?

545
00:30:22,560 --> 00:30:23,919
You're quite emotional.

546
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,280
No, I'm not.

547
00:30:26,159 --> 00:30:27,000
Wu.

548
00:30:28,679 --> 00:30:29,560
Do you like us?

549
00:30:29,639 --> 00:30:30,600
Do you like Doggy?

550
00:30:32,399 --> 00:30:33,360
Like?

551
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:37,480
What is "like"?

552
00:30:39,879 --> 00:30:41,480
See? She doesn't know what affection is.

553
00:30:41,560 --> 00:30:45,120
-I was just joking. -What is "like"?

554
00:30:48,199 --> 00:30:49,159
I like…

555
00:30:51,560 --> 00:30:52,639
Like…

556
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,000
-Wu? -Like.

557
00:30:58,080 --> 00:31:00,320
-Wu! -Like.

558
00:31:00,399 --> 00:31:02,320
-Okay. Forget it. -Does your head hurt again?

559
00:31:02,399 --> 00:31:04,600
-Like. -Don't think about it.

560
00:31:04,679 --> 00:31:06,399
-Stop thinking. -Like.

561
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:07,639
Like!

562
00:31:09,159 --> 00:31:10,439
Like!

563
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,280
Like.

564
00:31:15,959 --> 00:31:17,919
-What is "like"? -All right.

