Is that all?

579
00:32:15,159 --> 00:32:16,080
Thank you!

580
00:32:16,159 --> 00:32:17,159
Thank you.

581
00:32:18,679 --> 00:32:19,600
Wu.

582
00:32:19,679 --> 00:32:21,800
We'll get to see the family photo

583
00:32:21,879 --> 00:32:23,159
in a few days.

584
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:24,600
Family photo?

585
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:27,080
What is that?

586
00:32:27,159 --> 00:32:29,639
It's a photo of all of us together.

587
00:32:30,199 --> 00:32:31,600
-Dig in. -Wu.

588
00:32:31,679 --> 00:32:33,399
You have been here for five years now.

589
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:35,639
We don't know when your birthday is.

590
00:32:35,719 --> 00:32:37,080
I was thinking.

591
00:32:37,159 --> 00:32:38,879
We should use the date of your arrival

592
00:32:38,959 --> 00:32:40,159
as your birthday.

593
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:44,840
Wu, happy birthday.

594
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:51,240
What is a birthday?

595
00:32:51,320 --> 00:32:52,879
Birthday is the day

596
00:32:52,959 --> 00:32:54,360
you get to eat many good things.

597
00:32:54,439 --> 00:32:55,879
On my last birthday,

598
00:32:55,959 --> 00:32:57,600
Mom boiled two eggs for me.

599
00:32:58,320 --> 00:32:59,240
Two eggs.

600
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:00,760
Have some more.

601
00:33:01,320 --> 00:33:03,320
So is all this food for me?

602
00:33:03,399 --> 00:33:04,919
Well, yes. It's yours!

603
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:06,360
Eat.

604
00:33:06,439 --> 00:33:08,600
Mine.

605
00:33:09,439 --> 00:33:11,280
Mine.

606
00:33:57,199 --> 00:33:58,760
Doggy,

607
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:02,199
I left one last slice of meat for you.

608
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:12,679
Is it delicious?

609
00:34:13,759 --> 00:34:15,080
Say thank you, then.

610
00:34:15,679 --> 00:34:16,719
Thanks, Wu!

611
00:34:38,199 --> 00:34:39,600
Wu

612
00:34:39,679 --> 00:34:42,560
became our fondest family member.

613
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:46,639
But the blissful days

614
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:50,120
were soon interrupted

615
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:52,560
by a tragedy.

616
00:34:58,480 --> 00:34:59,319
Don't resist!
Move it!

617
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:04,880
Take all food and valuables.

618
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:06,120
Hurry up!

619
00:35:06,839 --> 00:35:08,360
Don't resist! Stay there!

620
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:13,120
That's our lamb!

621
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:14,080
Sit back down!

622
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:18,640
Gather these villagers later

623
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:20,319
and burn them alive.

624
00:35:20,400 --> 00:35:22,360
Leave no survivors, lest they expose us.

625
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:23,759
-Yes, sir! -Yes, sir!

626
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:31,920
The Huangyang shoulder pole Is soft and flexible

627
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:36,759
-Sisters and brothers -Hurry up.

628
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:39,120
They say Liuzhou--

629
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:41,600
This woman is…

630
00:35:42,319 --> 00:35:43,240
Show me your smile.
Boss!

631
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,120
Come.

632
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:53,000
Sir! Mercy, please. Take everything away.

633
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:54,799
But not her!

634
00:35:54,880 --> 00:35:55,839
She's still young.

635
00:35:55,920 --> 00:35:57,000
Don't take her away.

636
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:59,080
I'm begging you. Please!

637
00:35:59,160 --> 00:36:00,120
She's young. Spare her--

638
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:12,400
I'll kill you!

639
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:15,839
Doggy!

640
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:30,160
Boss, what do you think of her?

641
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:36,240
Stay right there!

642
00:36:39,080 --> 00:36:40,319
Doggy!

643
00:36:41,759 --> 00:36:44,240
What a cruel world!

644
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,520
This is not fair!

645
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:54,680
This is not fair!

646
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,000
Ms. Zhao.

647
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:06,440
For some reason, when I see you cry,

648
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:08,000
I feel sad.

649
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:10,960
This place hurts.

650
00:37:12,640 --> 00:37:14,279
I don't want to see you cry.

651
00:37:14,359 --> 00:37:16,680
I don't want to see Mr. Xu and Doggy

652
00:37:16,759 --> 00:37:17,720
getting hurt.

653
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,880
I want to see you smile.

654
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,759
I want to hear you sing.

655
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:26,120
Does this mean I like all of you?

656
00:37:26,200 --> 00:37:28,160
Ms. Zhao, I like you.

657
00:37:28,240 --> 00:37:29,200
I like Mr. Xu.

658
00:37:29,279 --> 00:37:30,400
I like Doggy.

659
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:33,759
Wu.

660
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:38,279
I envy you at times.

661
00:37:39,160 --> 00:37:41,359
You can stay ignorant.

662
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:49,680
Ms. Zhao, I don't want you to cry.

663
00:37:49,759 --> 00:37:50,960
I want you to be happy.

664
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:53,200
How can I make you happy?

665
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:56,480
My husband is dead.

666
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:01,400
What do you think can make me happy?

667
00:38:03,120 --> 00:38:04,279
Ms. Zhao.

668
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,080
All right.

669
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:13,640
I want all of them dead!

670
00:38:16,319 --> 00:38:17,319
That woman

671
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:18,680
is feisty.

672
00:38:18,759 --> 00:38:19,880
I like that.

673
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:36,920
All right, Ms. Zhao.

674
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:38,600
I'll kill all of them.

675
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:40,640
You pack a punch, lass.

676
00:38:40,720 --> 00:38:42,080
Are you trained?

677
00:39:52,759 --> 00:39:56,040
My mom thought that bloodbath

678
00:39:56,600 --> 00:40:00,040
would traumatize me.

679
00:40:00,120 --> 00:40:01,279
Little did she know

680
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,040
that for someone like me

681
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:06,759
who has one foot in the Outsiders' world,

682
00:40:08,040 --> 00:40:11,040
what I saw was something

683
00:40:11,120 --> 00:40:13,080
that defied all common sense.

